            <title>[THRIFT-400] Test failures in one language shouldn&apos;t keep test suites in other languages from firing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-400</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a really major issue for me as a maintainer. Test failures in one section of the codebase keep other tests from being run. So, for example, failing python tests keep me from confirming that tests pass on C++.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
